## Screenshots

All screenshots captured via Chrome DevTools Protocol (`Page.captureScreenshot`) with explicit device-metrics override to the requested viewport widths (1024 / 375), because `uvx rodney screenshot` does not expose a viewport option and `window.resizeTo` has no effect under headless Chrome.

| file | description |
|------|-------------|
| webr-1024x768-boot.png | webR target, boot state, 1024x768 viewport |
| webr-1024x768-full.png | webR target, loaded/idle state, 1024x768 viewport |
| webr-375x812-full.png  | webR target, loaded/idle state, 375x812 viewport |
| pyodide-1024x768-boot.png | Pyodide target, boot state, 1024x768 viewport |
| pyodide-1024x768-full.png | Pyodide target, loaded/idle state, 1024x768 viewport |
| pyodide-375x812-full.png  | Pyodide target, loaded/idle state, 375x812 viewport |

## Notes

- No `<style>` element present in either target; stylesheet loads via `<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">`.
- CSS custom property `--bt-font-family-ui` resolves in both targets, confirming `styles.css` loaded.
- Header/main/footer semantic layout is visible and ordered correctly in both targets.
- Subjective visual residual (color/spacing/typography/polish) was NOT evaluated; left for builder-vision-eval Phase 2.
